com.percussion.search
Class PSWSSearchResponse

java.lang.Object
  com.percussion.search.PSWSSearchResponse

public class PSWSSearchResponse
extends Object

This class is an object representation of search results returned by web services search. This class does not implement all functionality requried to support the schema defined by the WSDL for such results; it only provides the functionality required to process search results for the content explorer applet.

PSWSSearchResponse

public PSWSSearchResponse(Document doc,
                          String curUser)
                   throws com.percussion.design.objectstore.PSUnknownNodeTypeException
Construct this object from its xml representation. If curUser is supplied, then the sys_revision field will be calculated based on the current user if it is not found in the results.

Parameters:
doc - The document returned by a web services search request. May not be null.
curUser - Optionally supplied to calculate the sys_revision field value for each row in the results. If not null or empty, then it is compared against the value of the sys_contentcheckoutusername field, and if they match, the value of sys_tiprevision is used, otherwise the value of sys_currentrevision is used.
Throws:
com.percussion.design.objectstore.PSUnknownNodeTypeException - if an element in the source document is invalid.
